{"id": "bd-078", "title": "Local SLM: replace Haiku API with Qwen3-0.6B via llama.cpp", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "feature", "created_at": "2026-02-24T03:42:40.349729+00:00", "created_by": "davegraham", "updated_at": "2026-02-24T03:51:54.426917+00:00", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "labels": ["phase-1", "latency"], "description": "Replace Haiku API (~1200ms network round-trip) with local Qwen3-0.6B Q4_K_M.\n\n## Model Choice: Qwen3-0.6B (May 2025)\n- Q4_K_M GGUF: 0.48 GB \u2014 from bartowski/Qwen_Qwen3-0.6B-GGUF on HuggingFace\n- Newer architecture than Qwen2.5-0.5B, better instruction following\n- Qwen team positions it as BERT replacement for intent detection tasks\n- Estimated inference on Apple Silicon: 80-150ms (vs 1200ms API)\n\n## Memory Budget\n- Silero VAD: ~2 MB\n- Parakeet TDT int8: ~150 MB\n- Qwen3-0.6B Q4_K_M: ~480 MB\n- Python + deps: ~50 MB\n- Total: ~600 MB (well under 1GB target)\n\n## Implementation\n- Runtime: llama.cpp with Metal acceleration (or MLX for faster Apple Silicon)\n- Use GBNF grammar constraints to force valid JSON with known command names only\n- Eliminates hallucination \u2014 SLM picks from closed set, can't invent commands\n- Download: scripts/download-models.sh adds GGUF fetch\n- Integration: IntentParser._slm_path() swaps anthropic SDK for llama-cpp-python\n\n## Alternative worth exploring\n- Embedding classification (all-MiniLM-L6-v2, ~80MB ONNX, <5ms) for intent routing\n- Already have ONNX Runtime via sherpa-onnx\n- Hybrid: embeddings for intent classification + regex for parameter extraction\n- SLM only needed for mixed utterances with parameters regex can't parse"}
